loat: none;n  color:white;n}nn.h1,h1{n  color: white;n}nndiv#x-section-1.x-section.bg-color {n  border-radius: 10px 10px 0px 0px;n}","custom_js":"//n// No need to add script tagsn// here; simply get startedn// by writing JavaScript!n// Remember to save yourn// changes to see them :)n//nn","custom_js_mini":"","responsive_text":[]}";}s:17:"_cornerstone_data";a:1:{i:0;s:6296:"[{"_type":"section","title":"Section 3","elements":[{"_type":"row","_column_layout":"1/1","elements":[{"_type":"column","_active":true,"size":"1/1","elements":[{"_type":"text","elements":[],"content":"<h1>6 Ways to Grow your Email List by 3x</h1>n","text_align":"c"}]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]}]},{"_type":"row","title":"New Item 2","_column_layout":"1/1","elements":[{"_type":"column","_active":true,"size":"1/1","elements":[{"_type":"text","elements":[],"content":"<span id="intro">Learn marketing tactics to increase the amount of potential customers signing up to join your email list.</span>","text_align":"c"}],"padding":["20px","50px","0px","50px","unlinked"],"text_align":"","id":"intro"},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]}]}],"bg_type":"color","bg_color":"hsl(182, 55%, 58%)"},{"_type":"section","title":"Copy of Section 4","elements":[{"_type":"row","elements":[{"_type":"column","_active":true,"size":"1/1","elements":[{"_type":"line","elements":[],"line_color":"hsl(0, 0%, 100%)"},{"_type":"custom-headline","elements":[],"content":"Intro"},{"_type":"text","elements":[],"text_align":"l","content":"Hey business owners today I'm going to talk about 5 ways that you can increase the amount of people joining your email list.nnBefore we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is the fourth builder of you before we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is important to be building your email list everyday nnWhy is email important for my business?nnHaving someone who might be interested in your services give you your email, is now more valuable than ever. I would rather have 1000 emails of potential prospects, than 5000 home addresses of the same prospects to send physical mail to.nnTactic #1nOffer a discount on your servicesnnIf you were in the low ticket industry, offering a discount on your products or even in some cases a free product, is a great way to get your customers to visit your website with an ad or opt in the email so that you can target them later. nnIf you're hoping that people will care to opt into your newsletter without you offering anything additional to that, you're going to be sadly mistaken these days.nnFrom AB test we've run where we had email often forms offering nothing other than just updates and tips compared to opt in form is offering things such as a free download of some digital content, we saw often rates jumped by at least 5x.nnThis percentage increase varies depending on the industry, but overall giving something valuable to the consumer in exchange for them giving you their email, produces significantly more opt ins.nnTactic #2nHost an old-fashioned giveawaynnWhen you see those ads on Facebook giving away free things, (usually electronics), take a second to look at that next time. You're going to fine they want something in return, usually it's an email, share, or like.nnNow let's take it a step further rather than giving away just a free iPhone or something meaningless like that. Give away something that your ideal customers would want.nnYou might need to get a little creative.nnIf you're in the automotive industry, give away a new set of tires. If you're in the home remodeling space, give away a brand-new bathroom remodel. If you were in the restaurant industry (which is a little easier because who doesn't like to eat), offer a free dinner to one lucky winner.nnDepending on if you do your marketing right, this can generate hundreds if not thousands of people that would be interested in your product or service. You can quickly see how that would easily cover the cost of the prize to the winner.nnnTactic #3n include a downloadable PDF of whatever topic it is your blogging aboutnnThis one works very well too, especially if you're in the high ticket industry.nnLet's say you do plumbing and HVAC. nnA great example of this would be a 15 point checklist of things you can do as a homeowner to prevent damage to your plumbing and HVAC system.nnSome of you might be thinking right now, "But why would I tell my potential customers how not to need me?".nnEasy.nnGuess who's going to be top of mind when something does go wrong with their plumbing or HVAC?nnJoe Schmo's Plumbing on Yelp?nnOr you, the person who gave them a free resource without asking for anything but an email, and have been periodically providing free preventative care value to them via email?nnThe goal is to make yourself be the person I think about when they might need your services.nnnTactic #3nHost a giveawaynn Regardless of your industry, I'm sure there is something that you can find valuable to your potential customers to give away for free. Giveaways are not a thing of the past, they have worked extremely well for some of our clients.nnLet's say you're in the home inspection industry. You could be giving away a free home inspection to one person who enters.nnThe requirementsnMake sure that the competition is social, social proof will help out immensely in getting even more people to join a giveaway. The most common form of entering a game wa make sure that the competition is social, social proof will help out immensely in getting even more people to join a giveaway. The most common form of entering a giveaway,  is by asking your potential customers to Upton with their email address.nnThe less hurdles you make your audience jump through, and the more"}]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/3","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]},{"_type":"column","size":"1/1","_active":false,"elements":[]}],"_column_layout":"1/1"}],"padding":["20px","10%","45px","10%","unlinked"]}]";}s:20:"_cornerstone_excerpt";a:1:{i:0;s:713:"Learn marketing tactics to increase the amount of potential customers signing up to join your email list. Hey business owners today I&#8217;m going to talk about 5 ways that you can increase the amount of people joining your email list. Before we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is the fourth builder of you before we jump into the tips, I want to talk about why it is important to be building your email list everyday  Why is email important for my business? Having someone who might be interested in your services give you your email, is now more valuable than ever. I would rather have 1000 emails of potential prospects, than 5000 home addresses of the same prospects to send physical mail to.";}s:20:"_cornerstone_version";a:1:{i:0;s:5:"1.3.3";}}}